<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6781690-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7102"><num value="7102">§ 7102.</num><heading> Citizenship or noncitizen nationality</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Licenses and certificates of registry for individuals on documented vessels may be issued only to citizens or noncitizen nationals (as such term is described in section 308 of the Immigration and Nationality Act (<ref href="/us/usc/t8/s1408">8 U.S.C. 1408</ref>)) of the United States.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6781691-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/540">97 Stat. 540</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/119/60/dG/tLXXIII/s7301/b/1">Pub. L. 119–60, div. G, title LXXIII, § 7301(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="2025-12-18">Dec. 18, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/1751">139 Stat. 1751</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
